# ~/.zshrc.local — untracked machine-local secrets & private tooling.
# Copy to ~/.zshrc.local and fill in your own values. NEVER commit the real file.
#
# This is sourced last by zsh/.zshrc. Use it for:
#   - API keys / credentials
#   - private/work-only helpers you don't want in a public repo
#
# Non-secret, machine-specific paths (conda root, gcloud, etc.) do NOT belong
# here — put those in the tracked zsh-<machine> package instead.

# export AMP_API_KEY="..."

